<p>Consider the following HTML/CSS:</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>* {     box-sizing: border-box; }  .field {   overflow: auto; }    .field label {   float: left;   width: 80px; }  .field input {   display: block;   width: 100%; }</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;div class="field"&gt;   &lt;label&gt;Test&lt;/label&gt;   &lt;input type="text"&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>  <p>On both Firefox and Chromium, the result ends up looking like this:</p>  <p><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/7B9FO.png" alt="label above text input"></p>  <p>Instead, I would like the <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> to appear on the same line as the <code>&lt;label&gt;</code>. In other words, something like this:</p>  <p><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/pt2ps.png" alt="label beside text input"></p>  <p>Why isn't <code>float: left;</code> causing the label to appear to the left of the input?</p>